response.Q3: The cost for clicking on nodes varied between nodes.

response.Q0: Firstly, I made sure I didn't run out of time by clicking the closest possible node. Then I moved to far-end nodes to reveal their value as they had more value than mid and center nodes. This is to make sure I pay very little to get more and don't waste resources on less-paying nodes.
response.Q1: Yes. My approach initially was to click, pay, and reveal all nodes possible. However, I noticed that the paying or highest paying nodes are actually on the far end (edge), and started utilizing the strategy mentioned above. Avoid timeout and click far end, pay little for more, and don't click non-paying or less-paying nodes.
response.Q2: It wasn't difficult at all. The game was fascinating and intuitive. I followed my learning abilities to improve and formulate strategies along the way.
